ANC leaders are on the campaign trail ahead of next year's local government elections. The party's Secretary-General Ace Magashule visited the Ekurhuleni region Saturday. He's currently under the spotlight over corruption allegations against him. #eNCA reporter Siphamandla Goge is there. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC Secretary-General, Ace Magashule, says his critics are beneficiaries of procurement irregularities in the Free State. READ: Some ANC members gather to support Magashule He says former Free State Economic Development MEC, Mxolisi Dukwana, must equally account for his actions as he was part of the collective. "Some of those detractors are people who were beneficiaries of procurement. One day I will talk about them. They talk as if they never did anything in the Free State. He (Dukwana) must account. He was part of the collective of government. What went wrong was that he wanted to be a leader. He has been a leader because of us." The former MEC gave damning testimony against Magashule regarding tender fraud at the State Capture Inquiry. READ: I am not bothered by arrest reports: Magashule Magashule was on a campaign trail for the party in Ekurhuleni region on Saturday. Watch the video above for more details.